                    <div class="math-block">\\[\\mathbf{E} = \\lim_{q\\to 0}\\left(\\frac{F}{q}\\right)\\]</div>
                    <p>Electric field is independent of test charge q. Because in the equation of force charge there is test charge q present which is cancelled out by the denominator q. For the positive charge electric field is radially outward and for negative charge is radially inward. The magnitude of electric field by an charge depends upon the magnitude of that charge and distance of the point where we want to calculate the electric field.</p>
