                    </div>
                    <p>two charges - q and +q are separated by distance 2a. P is the point lies on the axis of dipole, where we want to calculate the electric field due to this dipole and r is the distance of point p from its centre.</p>
                    <p>Electric field at point p due to negative charge - q</p>
                    <div class="math-block">\\[E_{-q} = \\frac{kq}{(r - a)^2} \\hat{x}\\]</div>
                    <p>Electric field at point p due to positive charge q</p>
                    <div class="math-block">\\[E_{+q} = \\frac{kq}{(r + a)^2} (-\\hat{x}) \\qquad (r + a)\\text{ is the distance of point p from charge q}\\]</div>
